   {:e #blake3 "bf16a662515fe462a5d1808800b938815faff98c7990c87d0e29b1f572b4b94b" :a :db/ident :v :harvest/session-braid-user-1774124262 :op :assert}
   {:e #blake3 "bf16a662515fe462a5d1808800b938815faff98c7990c87d0e29b1f572b4b94b" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :recon/trace-0c049616ac90b874; Session entity: :recon/trace-1e0ae82e760a1eb6; Session entity: :recon/trace-3efd9038ac30b5db; Session entity: :task/t-04458171; UNIFICATION: Everything we discovered this session — materialized views, coherence gradient, self-steering, Lyapunov convergence — already exists in the spec. INV-BILATERAL-001 (L1 monotonic convergence), INV-GUIDANCE-010 (R(t) steepest descent), INV-COHERENCE-004 (Bures geodesic pursuit), INV-COHERENCE-013 (entropy second law), ADR-COHERENCE-003 (F(S) state/process decomposition). The spec designed a convergent dynamical system. The current implementation uses batch F(S) computation and graph-metric proxies for gradient. MaterializedViews + project_delta is not a new invention — it is the correct implementation of what the spec already requires. The EPIC should be: Implement the Convergence Engine. The performance fix is a side effect of implementing the spec correctly.; Session entity: :task/t-e8278e4a; Session entity: :task/t-2d4db20a; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-4: Session daemon as store server with ArcSwap. The daemon holds ArcSwap<Arc<Store>> (already specified in ADR-STORE-018). Exposes store operations (transact, query, fitness, entity-datoms, attribute-datoms) via Unix domain socket at .braid/braid.sock using JSON-lines protocol. ALSO exposes apply_command for full CLI command dispatch (backward compat). Eliminates 0.9s store deserialization per command. ArcSwap gives snapshot isolation: readers get Arc<Store> snapshot, writer constructs new Store via apply_tx then swaps atomically. No RwLock, no Mutex, lock-free by design. CLI thin client: detect socket, connect, send JSON, receive response, print. Fallback to embedded if no socket. Lifecycle: auto-start on first command, 2h idle shutdown (matching ST-1 staleness). CRDT periodic sync: every 5-10s, list txns/ for files newer than frontier, apply via apply_tx. This IS the multi-agent merge operation (INV-MERGE-001) — same algebra. No inotify needed.; THE COHERENCE GRADIENT — the single most accretive addition to the plan. MaterializedViews produce exact 7-dimensional ΔF(S) per transaction as a free side effect. This enables gradient-based R(t) routing: for each candidate action, project its fitness delta, select the action with maximum |ΔF(S)|. This is gradient ascent on the coherence manifold. It replaces learned weights (50+ observations, approximate) with exact computation (zero learning, correct by construction). The self-improvement loop from SEED.md S7 closes: the system doesn't just TRACK coherence, it NAVIGATES the coherence manifold along the steepest gradient. Every action selection is provably optimal given the current state. Calibration: record actual vs projected delta to detect when the gradient model diverges from reality (model error feedback loop).; Session entity: :task/t-0f5418b3; Session entity: :recon/trace-0ee69fd0647de8ed; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-3: Coherence gradient routing via project_delta. MaterializedViews::project_delta(hypothetical_datoms) -> FitnessDelta computes the exact 7-dimensional delta-F(S) = [dV,dC,dD,dH,dK,dI,dU] that a hypothetical transaction would produce, WITHOUT mutating state. This replaces the current R(t) implementation which uses graph metrics (pagerank, betweenness) as PROXY for the gradient. The spec (INV-GUIDANCE-010) already defines R(t) as 'steepest descent on the fitness landscape' — project_delta makes this computable exactly. For each candidate action: generate hypothetical datoms (observe->exploration datom, task close->status datom, harvest->harvest entity), call project_delta, rank by weighted_magnitude using same F(S) weights. The action with largest projected |delta-F(S)| is provably optimal. Record actual vs projected delta for calibration (model error feedback). This enables: (1) computed priorities replacing P0/P1/P2, (2) stigmergic multi-agent coordination via shared gradient field, (3) session planning as trajectory optimization on coherence manifold.; Session entity: :recon/trace-9e29cbb33b73f39c; Session entity: :task/t-56ec683b; Session entity: :recon/trace-b63cda511f5ff50b; Session entity: :task/t-72c580b2; Session entity: :task/t-1dab12ac; Session entity: :recon/trace-630258908523d684; Session entity: :recon/trace-e4c1349631477cc4; Session entity: :recon/trace-8a85e7a0cee7ee45; Session entity: :recon/trace-cbd41b68cbb80c5a; Session entity: :recon/trace-7e0197a635a8c1b9; Session entity: :recon/trace-43e9370d9d49b05e; Session entity: :task/t-e4ced73c; Session entity: :recon/trace-d862ad5360621848; Session entity: :recon/trace-e3bdf288be9db7f4; Session entity: :recon/trace-bd2fb7a046945121; Session entity: :recon/trace-d69e29beceb8b61c; Session entity: :recon/trace-ce09480411e51678; Session entity: :recon/trace-3ffbd992bdda6f49; Session entity: :recon/trace-9274cae638b48912; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-6: RFL-2/AR-2 migration to W_alpha. Currently main.rs post-command hook writes RFL-2 action predictions (line ~231) and AR-2 reconciliation traces (line ~249) to shared store via layout.write_tx(). Each write changes txn fingerprint, invalidating store.bin and all derived caches. Fix: in daemon mode, send telemetry to daemon W_alpha via socket. In embedded fallback, append to .braid/.cache/telemetry.jsonl (local journal, not txns/). R(t) weight learning still accesses prediction data via daemon query_view or journal replay. Session auto-detect (ST-1) also migrated: session metadata goes to W_alpha, only promoted to shared store on harvest --commit (via COTX-1 session rotation).; Session entity: :recon/trace-bd74b44107ebdab5; Session entity: :task/t-3610a861; Session entity: :recon/trace-71e0451626c5c07a; Session entity: :recon/trace-149885651b784fd3; All Durable Information as Datoms; Session entity: :task/t-aa61258c; Session entity: :task/t-5fad0a60; Session entity: :recon/trace-852760f7b296440a; THE DEEPEST INSIGHT: Materialized views + gradient routing + CRDT merge = a self-steering dynamical system with a Lyapunov convergence proof. F(S) is bounded [0,1], store is monotonically non-decreasing (G-Set), gradient routing selects F(S)-maximizing actions. Fixed point F(S)=1.0 is a provable attractor. Multi-agent coordination is EMERGENT — agents sharing a CRDT store follow the same gradient field, and each agent's action shifts the gradient for subsequent agents. No communication protocol, no task assignment, no orchestration needed. This is stigmergic coordination via shared coherence metrics. Priority assignment (P0/P1/P2) becomes COMPUTED, not human-assigned — the gradient projects each task's ΔF(S), and the task with maximum projected improvement IS the priority. The store specifies itself, measures itself, and steers itself toward its own coherence. The methodology becomes physics.; Session entity: :recon/trace-33127e7070a0da5e; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-2: Store::apply_tx incremental mutation. Add pub fn apply_tx(&mut self, datoms: &[Datom]) to Store. For each datom: (a) insert into self.datoms BTreeSet, (b) push to entity_index, attribute_index, (c) if Value::Ref push to vaet_index, (d) if Op::Assert push to avet_index, (e) update live_view with LWW resolution, (f) update MaterializedViews accumulators via views.observe(datom). For Op::Retract: do NOT add to avet_index; update live_view by scanning entity_datoms for next-latest assertion. Update frontier per agent. If any :db/* attributes present, rebuild Schema (rare path). ISOMORPHISM INVARIANT: for any S and D, S.clone().apply_tx(D) == Store::from_datoms(S.datom_set() union D). This is the fundamental correctness property — property-testable. Complexity: O(k) per transaction where k=datom count, vs O(n) for full from_datoms rebuild. Implements ADR-STORE-005 (indexes maintained incrementally).; Session entity: :recon/trace-8456654f5810efd5; Session entity: :recon/trace-d06b7833fb2ee664; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-7: BUG-RECON-FP — harvest reconciliation false positive gate. DAEMON-1 (t-0a1b5c4e) was auto-closed by harvest reconciliation with criteria_confidence=0%. The task merely traced to INV-STORE-001 which has existing impl links, but the SPECIFIC acceptance criteria (apply_tx method) are NOT implemented. Fix: in task.rs audit_tasks_from_store, if criteria_confidence is Some(v) and v < 0.1, cap overall confidence at 0.5 (below 0.7 auto-close threshold). If criteria_confidence is None, reduce confidence by 0.3 penalty. Include both spec_coverage and criteria_confidence in close reason.; Session entity: :recon/trace-18e79a5d3e8a5f3e; Session entity: :task/t-9df408f3; Session entity: :task/t-f1969e12; CRDT SYNC as external mutation model — the daemon is a CRDT replica, not a filesystem watcher. The store is a G-Set CvRDT (INV-STORE-001). Merge is set union, commutative, associative, idempotent. The daemon holds Store_daemon in memory; disk holds Store_disk. Periodic sync: daemon lists txns/ for files newer than its frontier, applies them via apply_tx. This IS the merge operation — same algebraic structure as multi-agent merge (INV-MERGE-001). No inotify, no OS-specific APIs, no missed events, no race conditions. The daemon is just another replica that periodically pulls. Sync trigger: every 5-10s background, or on-demand before consistency-critical operations. ArcSwap<Arc<Store>> (ADR-STORE-018) provides snapshot isolation — readers never blocked by sync. This is the most axiologically aligned solution because it uses the system's own coordination primitive (CRDT merge) rather than introducing an external mechanism (filesystem events).; Session entity: :task/t-6e170123; Session entity: :recon/trace-35856c7b7243d080; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-8: Spec deprecation — store as source of truth. All 378 spec elements already in braid store (bootstrapped during init). Markdown files in spec/, docs/design/ADRS.md, docs/guide/ are deprecated bootstrap scaffolding. All spec changes must go through braid CLI (spec create, observe, transact). Markdown should become read-only projections generated from store via braid spec export. CLAUDE.md references should point to braid CLI commands not markdown files. This prevents methodology violations where agents edit markdown instead of transacting through the store.; BUG: Harvest reconciliation false positive — auto-closed DAEMON-1 (t-0a1b5c4e) with 0% criteria_confidence. The task traces to INV-STORE-001 which has impl links (the existing store), but the SPECIFIC acceptance criteria (apply_tx method, O(k) mutation, isomorphism property) are NOT implemented. The reconciliation should NOT auto-close tasks with criteria_confidence=0%. Fix: add minimum criteria_confidence threshold (e.g., 0.3) to the auto-close gate. Task spec_coverage alone is necessary but not sufficient for auto-closure.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ced456488e1461e0; Session entity: :recon/trace-d31b88b8de45664e; Session entity: :task/t-5a41a6b9; Session entity: :recon/trace-33f75281558e4377; DEEP ANALYSIS: External mutation detection — first principles interrogation. The question is not 'how does the daemon detect external writes' but 'what is the correct coordination model when multiple processes share an append-only datom store?' Four candidate models: (A) Filesystem watch (inotify) — daemon polls OS for file events. Reactive, OS-dependent, misses events during daemon downtime, complex edge cases (rename vs write, buffering). (B) Transaction notification protocol — writers notify daemon via socket after writing. Requires all writers to know about daemon. Violates the filesystem-as-coordination principle. (C) Frontier comparison — on each query, daemon compares its frontier with disk frontier. If disk is ahead, apply new txns. Lazy, correct, but adds latency to reads. (D) The store IS the coordination — this is the DDIS answer. The shared store in txns/ is the coordination substrate (ADR-STORE-006). The daemon is a local cache, not the authority. On any operation that requires freshness (transact, merge), the daemon checks disk. On reads (query, status), the daemon serves from memory (possibly stale by one transaction). The staleness is bounded and disclosed.; Session entity: :recon/trace-5f6796feb3100ca7; Session entity: :recon/trace-3b3c59745485355c; Session entity: :recon/trace-977f85ed78b03dd2; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-5: W_alpha agent working set for FD-012 compliance. INV-STORE-013 defines W_alpha as private agent working set: local_datoms invisible to other agents, excluded from merge, promoted via explicit commit. The daemon holds W_alpha in memory. Operational telemetry (RFL-2 predictions, AR-2 traces, session auto-detect) goes to W_alpha instead of shared store txns/. Classification function: is_operational(rationale) -> bool. W_alpha datoms visible via query_view(store) = store union W_alpha. Flushed to .braid/.cache/working_set.bin every 60s and on shutdown for crash recovery (PD-003). On harvest --commit: optionally promote selected W_alpha datoms to shared store. KEY EFFECT: RFL-2 no longer writes to txns/, fingerprint stable across read commands, store.bin cache hits consistently. This is THE fix for the 30s cache invalidation cascade.; DEEP REVIEW — Three architectural gaps in DAEMON EPIC that change the task design:\n\nGAP 1: INCREMENTAL F(S) IS THE REAL FIX, NOT JUST CACHING. The daemon caches F(S) but doesn't fix the 29s cold-compute. When a knowledge mutation occurs (observe, harvest), the daemon still takes 29s to recompute. The fix: 5 of 7 F(S) components (V, C, H, I, U) can be maintained as running accumulators updated in O(k) per transaction. D (drift via live_projections) can use incremental counters per namespace. K (contradiction) can use a conflict index BTreeMap<(EntityId,Attribute,TxId), Vec<Value>>. This makes F(S) recomputation O(k) not O(n). The daemon holds these accumulators in memory. This should be DAEMON-4b, not optional — without it the first status after every observe still takes 29s.\n\nGAP 2: DAEMON AS STORE SERVER, NOT CLI WRAPPER. The daemon shouldn't wrap CLI commands — it should expose the Store directly. Any process (CLI, MCP, TUI, future agents) connects and issues datom operations (transact, query, fitness). The CLI becomes a thin client that translates user commands into store operations. This is architecturally cleaner and enables the TUI (SEED.md S8 Interface Layer 5) and multi-agent coordination (SEED.md S3) without additional infrastructure.\n\nGAP 3: EXTERNAL STORE MUTATION DETECTION. If another agent writes directly to txns/ (bypassing daemon), the daemon's in-memory store is stale. Need filesystem watch (inotify/kqueue) on txns/ directory. When new files appear, daemon applies them via apply_tx. This preserves the filesystem-as-coordination-model from ADR-STORE-006.; Session entity: :task/t-d6e3a751; Coherence Gradient Convergence — F(S) is a Lyapunov function for gradient-routed action selection; Session entity: :recon/trace-63c64e3e188e0781; Session entity: :recon/trace-054b064c8fe8ef0c; Session entity: :recon/trace-8b98e0450442d682; CONVERGENCE ENGINE OBS-1: MaterializedViews struct as Store field. F(S) components (V,C,D,H,K,I,U), coherence metrics (Phi, beta_1, live projections), task counts (open/closed/ready/blocked), and methodology score M(t) should all be fields of the Store struct, maintained incrementally by apply_tx — exactly as the 5 existing indexes (EAVT, AEVT, VAET, AVET, LIVE) already are. The views are serialized in store.bin via Serde (already derived on Store). On cache hit: instant F(S) read. On cache miss: views rebuilt alongside indexes in the same O(n) from_datoms pass. No separate 29s compute_fitness call ever needed. This implements INV-BILATERAL-001 L1 (F(S) monotonically non-decreasing) as a structural property: each apply_tx produces the exact delta. Accumulators: V=HashMap<EntityId,i64> spec->max_depth. C=HashSet<EntityId> impl targets. D=(intent_count,spec_count,impl_count) namespace counters. H=methodology telemetry counters. K=HashMap<(EntityId,Attribute),BTreeMap<TxId,Vec<Value>>> conflict index. I=HashMap<EntityId,(bool,bool)> has_impl/has_task. U=(sum_confidence:f64,count:usize) running average. Each accumulator updated in O(1) per datom by classifying the datom's attribute.; Session entity: :recon/trace-1e801577a5f8d50b; Session entity: :recon/trace-d722b4197fea0676; Session entity: :recon/trace-0de9c94039cc3351; Session entity: :recon/trace-0851394595aa4de6; Session entity: :recon/trace-46e8544409091cfe; Session entity: :recon/trace-d374c9ef40421d0c; Session entity: :task/t-bb5445f2; Session entity: :recon/trace-1a387a2687cf70ff; Session entity: :recon/trace-f2e8e74f3b2511c6; Session entity: :recon/trace-49949c8659a31947; METHODOLOGY VIOLATION: Edited docs/design/ADRS.md and spec/01-store.md directly instead of transacting ADR revision into the braid store. The markdown spec files are bootstrap scaffolding — the store is the source of truth. All spec changes must go through braid spec create / braid observe / braid transact. The markdown files should be deprecated projections (like HARVEST.md was), not mutable source documents.; Session entity: :recon/trace-d0ba2a937330a0c2; Session entity: :recon/trace-902153447a10f9aa; Session entity: :recon/trace-b28e7ae6285ec7db; Session entity: :recon/trace-e04ccde3c58c5064; Session entity: :recon/trace-d8f8ad695614704d; Session entity: :recon/trace-cb6706b414b955d4; Session entity: :recon/trace-f506d58a746bf029; Session entity: :recon/trace-f17dd2661e416f29; Session entity: :task/t-05f6dca2; PROFOUND INSIGHT: Materialized views as Store fields — the daemon is NOT the performance fix. The real fix is maintaining F(S), coherence, task counts, M(t) as incremental accumulators inside the Store struct, updated by apply_tx alongside the existing 5 indexes. This makes all derived values O(1) reads and O(k) updates. The views are serialized in store.bin automatically (Serde). Even in embedded mode with cache miss, the views are rebuilt during from_datoms (same O(n) pass that builds indexes). No separate 29s compute_fitness pass ever needed again. The daemon STILL adds value: (1) eliminates 0.9s I/O via ArcSwap in-memory, (2) enables W_alpha for operational telemetry, (3) CRDT periodic sync for multi-agent. But the daemon is Phase 1 polish, not Phase 0 correctness. Phase 0 = MaterializedViews in Store. This is the axiologically correct factoring because it uses the system's own abstraction (materialized views, already used for LIVE index) rather than introducing external mechanisms (caching, daemons, background threads).; Session entity: :task/t-451e387b; Session entity: :recon/trace-098db2b1bf92dfcf; Session entity: :task/t-e545d28b; Session entity: :recon/trace-885ea0f2834f363d; Session entity: :recon/trace-aba6fc7276ceb70c; Session entity: :recon/trace-aecd2587607953d9\nSession entity: :task/t-765681bc" :op :assert}
